'''Ousmane Diomande''' (born 4 December 2003) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Sporting CP]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

==Club career==
===Midtjylland===
Diomande is a youth product of the Ivorian club Olympic Sport Abobo, having joined at the age of 10.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sapobrasil.com.br/desporto/artigos/quem-o-garante-e-o-homem-que-descobriu-o-novo-central-do-sporting-para-o-futebol-diomande-sera-um-dos-melhores-do-mundo|title=Quem o garante é o homem que 'descobriu' o novo central do Sporting para o futebol: "Diomande será um dos melhores do mundo"|website=SAPO Brasil|access-date=10 February 2023|archive-date=10 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230210210050/https://sapobrasil.com.br/desporto/artigos/quem-o-garante-e-o-homem-que-descobriu-o-novo-central-do-sporting-para-o-futebol-diomande-sera-um-dos-melhores-do-mundo|url-status=dead}}</ref> He moved to the youth academy of the Danish club [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] in January 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/mercato-arsenal-a-la-lutte-avec-le-sporting-lisbone-pour-une-pepite-ivoirienne/|title=Mercato : Arsenal à la lutte avec le Sporting Lisbone pour une pépite ivoirienne|first=Jules|last=Dia|date=January 19, 2023|access-date=10 February 2023|archive-date=10 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230210210049/https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/mercato-arsenal-a-la-lutte-avec-le-sporting-lisbone-pour-une-pepite-ivoirienne/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Diomande joined the Portuguese club [[C.D. Mafra|Mafra]] on loan on 5 August 2022 on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportherning.dk/artikel/ad3887e7-fef8-4675-98fe-22df4643d5c9/|title=Spilletid forude: FCM udlejer forsvarstalent til portugisisk klub|website=Sport Herning}}</ref> The next day he made his professional debut with Mafra in a 3–1 [[Liga Portugal 2]] loss to [[U.D. Oliveirense|Oliveirense]] on 6 August 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jornaldemafra.pt/2022/08/06/futebol-cd-mafra-comeca-o-campeonato-com-uma-derrota-frente-ao-oliveirense/|title=Futebol &#124; CD Mafra começa o campeonato com uma derrota frente ao Oliveirense – Jornal de Mafra Futebol &#124; CD Mafra começa o campeonato com uma derrota frente ao Oliveirense|date=August 6, 2022}}</ref>

===Sporting===
Thanks to impressive performances with Mafra, Diomande's loan was cut short halfway through the season and he transferred to [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Sporting CP]] on 31 January 2023, signing a contract until June 2027 for a fee of €7.5 million, which could rise to €12.5 million with add-ons. Midtjylland is also owed 20% of the profit Sporting receives from a future transfer. Diomande's release clause was set at €80 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=15 November 2023 |title=Sporting divulga números do mercado de transferências |trans-title=Sporting discloses transfer market numbers |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/sporting-divulga-numeros-do-mercado-de-transferencias-2023111515540109816 |access-date=15 November 2023 |website= |publisher=A Bola |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

Diomande made his debut for the [[Lisbon]] club on 7 February, coming off the bench to replace [[Matheus Reis]] on the final minutes of a 1–0 league victory away at [[Rio Ave F.C.|Rio Ave]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 February 2023 |title=Chermiti goal earns Sporting CP three points |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2023-02-07/chermiti-goal-earns-sporting-cp-three-points |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Sporting CP |language=en}}</ref> Two weeks later, he made his first start for the ''Lions'', in a 3–2 league victory away at [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]], where he was replaced by [[Jerry St. Juste|Jeremiah St. Juste]] on the 71st minute.<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 February 2023 |title=Sporting CP beat GD Chaves 2-3 |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2023-02-21/sporting-cp-beat-gd-chaves-2-3 |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Sporting CP |language=en}}</ref> Diomande made his [[UEFA|European]] debut on 9 March, coming off the bench to replace [[Ricardo Esgaio]] on the 77th minute of a 2–2 draw at home to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]] round of 16 first leg.<ref>{{Cite web |date=9 March 2023 |title=London calling for Sporting CP after 2-2 first leg with Arsenal |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2023-03-09/london-calling-sporting-cp-after-2-2-first-leg-arsenal |access-date=24 September 2023 |website= |publisher=Sporting CP |language=en}}</ref> Eight days later, on the return fixture in the [[Emirates Stadium]], Diomande started and played the full match, as Sporting drew 1–1 and eliminated Arsenal through [[penalty shootout]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 March 2023 |title=Sporting CP outstrike Gunners in Europa League shootout |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2023-03-17/sporting-cp-outstrike-gunners-europa-league-shootout |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Sporting CP |language=en}}</ref> The Ivorian scored his first goal for the ''Lions'' on 21 May 2023, in the [[Lisbon derby]], out-jumping [[Álex Grimaldo]] to head a [[Nuno Santos (footballer, born 1995)|Nuno Santos]] corner into the net, making the score 2–0 for Sporting; however, Benfica went on to salvage a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 May 2023 |title=Derby victory denied by late equaliser |url=https://www.sporting.pt/en/news/football/main-team/2023-05-22/derby-victory-denied-late-equaliser |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Sporting CP |language=en}}</ref> Sporting CP finished the [[2022–23 Sporting CP season|2022–23 season]] in 4th place in the Primeira Liga, qualifying for the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League]] group stage.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Classificação Liga |trans-title=League Classification |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/resultadoseclassificacoes/anterior/128/394556/portugal/primeira-liga |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=Maisfutebol |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

On 21 September 2023, Diomande scored his first goal in European competitions, through a 84th minute winner in a 2–1 victory away at [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] in the UEFA Europa League.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=21 September 2023 |title=Análise: Gyokeres e Diomande colocaram fim à malapata na Áustria |trans-title=Analysis: Gyokeres and Diomande put an end to the bad luck in Austria |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/liga-europa/artigos/analise-gyokeres-e-diomande-colocaram-fim-a-malapata-na-austria |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

On 23 January 2026, Diomande extended his contract with Sporting CP until June 2030.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 January 2026 |title=Ousmane Diomande renova até 2030 |trans-title=Ousmane Diomande renews until 2030 |url=https://www.sporting.pt/pt/noticias/futebol/equipa-principal/2026-01-23/ousmane-diomande-renova-ate-2030 |access-date=26 January 2026 |publisher=[[Sporting CP]] |language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
Diomande was called up to the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]] for a set of [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]] matches in September 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fifciv.com/?q=matchs-civ-les-civ-mal-voici-les-25-el%C3%A9phants-retenus|title=Matchs CIV-LES & CIV-MAL : Voici Les 25 Eléphants Retenus|website=fifciv.com|accessdate=30 August 2023}}</ref> He debuted in a 1–0 win over [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] on 9 September 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|title=La Côte d'Ivoire bat le Lesotho sur le score de 1 but à 0 au stade Laurent Pokou de San Pedro. Le but ivoirien a été inscrit par Ibrahim Sangaré à la 16e minute.|first=R. T. I.|last=Info|date=September 9, 2023|website=RTI Info|access-date=9 September 2023|archive-date=4 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231004142837/https://www.rti.info/depeches/2023/9/9/la-cote-divoire-bat-le-lesotho-sur-le-score-de-1-but-a-0-au-stade-laurent-pokou-de-san-pedro-le-but-ivoirien-a-ete-inscrit-par-ibrahim-sangare-a-la-16e-minute|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In December 2023, Diomande was named to the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]]. Despite only featuring for first two group stage matches against [[Guinea-Bissau national football team|Guinea-Bissau]] and [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]], Ivory Coast ended up winning the tournament on 11 February, after defeating Nigeria 2–1 in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations final|final]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl|title=LA LISTE|publisher=[[Ivorian Football Federation]]|date=28 December 2023|access-date=16 January 2024|language=pt|via=[[Facebook]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf|title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE|publisher=Confederation of African Football|date=5 January 2024}}</ref>

Diomande was included in the list of Ivorian players selected by coach [[Emerse Faé]] to participate in the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=Nicolas Pépé et Simon Adingra absents, Wilfried Zaha de retour : la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la CAN |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Nicolas-pepe-et-simon-adingra-absents-wilfried-zaha-de-retour-la-liste-de-la-cote-d-ivoire-pour-la-can/1615689 |website=www.lequipe.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref><ref>{{cite web|date=9 December 2025 |language=fr |title=CAN 2025: la liste de la Côte d'Ivoire, tenante du titre, avec le retour de Wilfried Zaha |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20251209-can-2025-la-liste-de-la-c%C3%B4te-d-ivoire-tenante-du-titre-avec-le-retour-de-wilfried-zaha |website=www.rfi.fr}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

On May 15, 2026, Diomandé was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Fae]] in his list of 26 players in order to compete in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

== Style of play ==
As a central defender, he has the ability to play out from the back and drive the team forward, allowing his team to play out of trouble and turn defense to attack quickly.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Player Analysis: Ousmane Diomande |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/player-analysis-ousmane-diomande/ |access-date=2023-11-24 |website=Breaking The Lines |language=en-GB}}</ref> His main strengths are his physicality, his vision and his speed, but he has also notable short passing, dribbling, positioning, anticipation and tackling attributes.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kulig |first=Jacek |date=2023-06-30 |title=Ousmane Diomande: Sporting CP's Ivorian Jewel by Saul Morris |url=https://footballtalentscout.net/2023/06/30/ousmane-diomande-sporting-cps-ivorian-jewel-by-saul-morris/ |access-date=2023-11-24 |website=Football Talent Scout |language=en-US |archive-date=24 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231124132557/https://footballtalentscout.net/2023/06/30/ousmane-diomande-sporting-cps-ivorian-jewel-by-saul-morris/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=19-year-old Ousmane Diomande is The Next Big Defender.. |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3X9R3FPGnCk |access-date=2023-11-24 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Um muro difícil de superar com olhinhos nos pés: o que dizem os números de Ousmane Diomande e como explicam a cobiça europeia |url=https://tribuna.expresso.pt/o-que-dizem-os-teus-numeros/2023-09-27-Um-muro-dificil-de-superar-com-olhinhos-nos-pes-o-que-dizem-os-numeros-de-Ousmane-Diomande-e-como-explicam-a-cobica-europeia-70fdd908 |access-date=2023-11-24 |website=Tribuna Expresso |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

